<tt>Sun Aug 17  0:34:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
How to begin......<br>
Has taken 5 days to get this far down the threads in catching up.  Am pleasantly surprised by what I've found on this thread.  Somewhat like Tom, I don't claim the mantle of warrior.  Never did, even before the combat vs REMF issue started heating up, say 15 years ago.  Was shot at maybe six times and never was in a postion of extreme danger or of firing a weapon in anger; though I know I'm responsible for some number of dead through my targeting.  Will take up the student's position across the fire if I may, and hopefully listen well with both my mind and heart; so that I may learn from my brothers' wisdom during my life's journey.  My closest Native American ancestor is 250 years back, and I can't claim to know Indian ways more than superficially, but as one who is born on &quot;Turtle Island&quot; of people here for years, am not quite European either.  I think part of the trouble with white Americans is that many of us don't really know where we came from, who we really are or what we are becoming.  There I go again.  Will shut up for a change. 
